    <template id="page_odr_procedural_rules" name="ODR procedural rules">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
            <div id="wrap">
                <t t-set="bn_nav_inner" t-value="True"/>
                <t t-call="bharatnyay_website.bn_public_nav"/>
                <div class="bn-about-page">
                    <header class="bn-about-hero text-lg-start bn-hero-split">
                        <div class="container">
                            <p class="bn-hash mb-3">Education · Rules posture</p>
                            <h1><span class="text-orange">Procedural</span> rules in digitised arbitration &amp; mediation</h1>
                            <p class="mx-lg-0">Parties adopt institutional rulebooks (<em>e.g.</em>, SIAC, ICC, ICA, UNCITRAL) or bespoke charters. BharatNyay encodes timelines, pleadings uploads, arbitrator challenges, confidentiality, interim relief interplay, and tribunal secretary roles so software mirrors the rule narrative — not substitutes it.</p>
                        </div>
                    </header>
                    <section class="bn-about-body">
                        <div class="container bn-prose bn-prose-wide">
                            <h2>What “procedural rules” govern on-platform activity?</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Commencement &amp; joinder:</strong> request for arbitration, claimant roster, ancillary parties, consolidating related facilities.</li>
                                <li><strong>Seat &amp; language:</strong> defaults from your contractual clause repository; deviations recorded with tribunal leave.</li>
                                <li><strong>Evidence &amp; discovery:</strong> document production calendars, objections, supplemental bundles before hearing weeks.</li>
                                <li><strong>Virtual hearings etiquette:</strong> oath, recording disclosure, interpreters, caucus blackout windows.</li>
                                <li><strong>Costs &amp; deposits:</strong> advance on arbitrator fees — surfaced for finance sign-off workflows.</li>
                                <li><strong>Settlement homologation:</strong> mediated minutes converted to consent awards with registrar reminders.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="text-muted small">Deploy with issuer counsel approving the governing rules text; configure BharatNyay to flag breaches of internal SLAs referencing those rules.</p>
                            <div class="bn-odr-proto-grid mt-4">
                                <a href="/odr/proceedings" class="bn-odr-proto-chip">Proceedings ladder</a>
                                <a href="/odr/model-clause" class="bn-odr-proto-chip">Model clause cues</a>
                                <a href="/odr/standards" class="bn-odr-proto-chip">Standards overview</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                </div>
                <div class="bn-landing-root"><t t-call="bharatnyay_website.bn_public_footer"/></div>
            </div>
        </t>
    </template>

