                            <h1><span class="text-orange">Code</span> of ethics for neutrals online</h1>
                            <p class="mx-lg-0">Impartiality, independence, diligent preparation, avoidance of undue delay, nondisclosure obligations, equitable treatment of witnesses, and remuneration transparency underpin legitimate ODR — aligned globally with institute codes BharatNyay customers typically adopt.</p>
                        </div>
                    </header>
                    <section class="bn-about-body">
                        <div class="container bn-prose bn-prose-wide">
                            <h2>Operational hooks inside BharatNyay</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Conflict disclosure questionnaires before arbitrator acceptance clicks.</li>
                                <li>Immutable logs separating caucus vs joint session artefacts.</li>
                                <li>Fee schedules versioned beside appointment letters.</li>
                                <li>Grievance escalation paths for unethical conduct surfaced to supervisory counsel.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <div class="bn-odr-proto-grid mt-4">
                                <a href="/odr/standards/neutral-appointment" class="bn-odr-proto-chip">Appointment protocol</a>
